{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":606,"text":"Traditional prescriptions for growth\nin Africa are not working very well."},{"time":6519,"text":"After one trillion dollars\nin African development-related aid"},{"time":10971,"text":"in the last 60 years,"},{"time":13099,"text":"real per capita income today\nis lower than it was in the 1970s."},{"time":18867,"text":"Aid is not doing too well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21170,"text":"In response,"},{"time":22588,"text":"the Bretton Woods institutions --\nthe IMF and the World Bank --"},{"time":26672,"text":"pushed for free trade not aid,"},{"time":30226,"text":"yet the historical record\nshows little empirical evidence"},{"time":34451,"text":"that free trade leads to economic growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38561,"text":"The newly prescribed \nsilver bullet is microcredit."},{"time":42460,"text":"We seem to be fixated\non this romanticized idea"},{"time":46177,"text":"that every poor peasant in Africa\nis an entrepreneur."},{"time":50031,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":53328,"text":"Yet my work and travel\nin 40-plus countries across Africa"},{"time":58698,"text":"have taught me that most people\nwant jobs instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63615,"text":"My solution: Forget micro-entrepreneurs."},{"time":67190,"text":"Let's invest in building\npan-African titans"},{"time":70836,"text":"like Sudanese businessman Mo Ibrahim."},{"time":75061,"text":"Mo took a contrarian bet on Africa when\nhe founded Celtel International in '98"},{"time":80959,"text":"and built it into a mobile \ncellular provider"},{"time":84494,"text":"with 24 million subscribers\nacross 14 African countries by 2004."},{"time":92076,"text":"The Mo model might be better\nthan the everyman entrepreneur model,"},{"time":95745,"text":"which prevents an effective means\nof diffusion and knowledge-sharing."},{"time":99741,"text":"Perhaps we are not at a stage in Africa"},{"time":102357,"text":"where many actors and small enterprises\nleads to growth through competition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107624,"text":"Consider these two alternative scenarios."},{"time":111034,"text":"One: You loan 200 dollars \nto each of 500 banana farmers"},{"time":117070,"text":"allowing them to dry \ntheir surplus bananas"},{"time":119967,"text":"and fetch 15 percent more revenue\nat the local market."},{"time":124295,"text":"Or two: You give 100,000 dollars\nto one savvy entrepreneur"},{"time":130477,"text":"and help her set up a factory\nthat yields 40 percent additional income"},{"time":135695,"text":"to all 500 banana farmers\nand creates 50 additional jobs."},{"time":141747,"text":"We invested in the second scenario,"},{"time":144371,"text":"and backed 26-year-old\nKenyan entrepreneur Eric Muthomi"},{"time":148867,"text":"to set up an agro-processing\nfactory called Stawi"},{"time":152536,"text":"to produce gluten-free\nbanana-based flour and baby food."},{"time":158242,"text":"Stawi is leveraging economies of scale"},{"time":161283,"text":"and using modern manufacturing processes\nto create value for not only its owners"},{"time":166164,"text":"but its workers, who have\nan ownership in the business."},{"time":170579,"text":"Our dream is to take an Eric Muthomi\nand try to help him become a Mo Ibrahim,"},{"time":176708,"text":"which requires skill, financing,\nlocal and global partnerships,"},{"time":181855,"text":"and extraordinary perseverance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184525,"text":"But why pan-African?"},{"time":187590,"text":"The scramble for Africa\nduring the Berlin Conference of 1884 --"},{"time":192188,"text":"where, quite frankly, we Africans\nwere not exactly consulted --"},{"time":196924,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause) --"},{"time":203542,"text":"resulted in massive fragmentation"},{"time":206003,"text":"and many sovereign states\nwith small populations:"},{"time":208534,"text":"Liberia, four million;\nCape Verde, 500,000."},{"time":211576,"text":"Pan-Africa gives you one billion people,"},{"time":214315,"text":"granted across 55 countries\nwith trade barriers and other impediments,"},{"time":218472,"text":"but our ancestors traded\nacross the continent"},{"time":221705,"text":"before Europeans drew lines around us."},{"time":224282,"text":"The pan-African opportunities\noutweigh the challenges,"},{"time":227719,"text":"and that's why we're expanding\nStawi's markets from just Kenya"},{"time":231155,"text":"to Algeria, Nigeria, Ghana,\nand anywhere else that will buy our food."},{"time":235520,"text":"We hope to help solve food security,\nempower farmers, create jobs,"},{"time":239514,"text":"develop the local economy,\nand we hope to become rich in the process."},{"time":243948,"text":"While it's not the sexiest approach,"},{"time":246167,"text":"and maybe it doesn't\nachieve the same feel-good"},{"time":248415,"text":"as giving a woman 100 dollars \nto buy a goat on kiva.org,"},{"time":252306,"text":"perhaps supporting fewer,\nhigher-impact entrepreneurs"},{"time":256231,"text":"to build massive businesses\nthat scale pan-Africa"},{"time":259204,"text":"can help change this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262364,"text":"The political freedom\nfor which our forebearers fought"},{"time":266918,"text":"is meaningless without economic freedom."},{"time":271326,"text":"We hope to aid this fight\nfor economic freedom"},{"time":274136,"text":"by building world-class businesses,"},{"time":276597,"text":"creating indigenous wealth,"},{"time":278571,"text":"providing jobs that we\nso desperately need,"},{"time":281705,"text":"and hopefully helping achieve this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285792,"text":"Africa shall rise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288694,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290250,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":297471,"text":"Tom Rielly: So Sangu, of course,\nthis is strong rhetoric."},{"time":301465,"text":"You're making 100 percent contrast\nbetween microcredit"},{"time":304460,"text":"and regular investment\nand growing regular investment."},{"time":308825,"text":"Do you think there is\na role for microcredit at all?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311277,"text":"Sangu Delle: I think there is a role."},{"time":313539,"text":"Microcredit has been a great,\ninnovative way"},{"time":316093,"text":"to expand financial access\nto the bottom of the pyramid."},{"time":320063,"text":"But for the problems we face in Africa,"},{"time":322315,"text":"when we are looking\nat the Marshall Plan"},{"time":324204,"text":"to revitalize war-torn Europe,"},{"time":325821,"text":"it was not full of donations of sheep."},{"time":327904,"text":"We need more than just microcredit."},{"time":329626,"text":"We need more than just give 200 dollars."},{"time":331757,"text":"We need to build big businesses,\nand we need jobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334831,"text":"TR: Very good. Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337227,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}